If you look at the "Other Linker Flags" section of your Xcode settings, you should see several settings. If you remove
-Xlinker -S -Xlinker -x -Xlinker -dead_strip
you should see more symbols when you run your app, and so find it easier to set breakpoints.

body:
If you look at the "Other Linker Flags" section of your Xcode settings, you should see several settings. If you remove 
`
-Xlinker
-S
-Xlinker
-x
-Xlinker
-dead_strip
`
you should see more symbols when you run your app, and so find it easier to set breakpoints.
